{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"99r2x1rqn5bjkis60k7vu7t","title":"Convert Angle to Vector2","desc":"","updated":1681658615832,"created":1676142818024,"custom":{},"fname":"math.geometry.convert-angle-to-vector2","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"f0d05e6aa1da17dba3594e65ada4e9d0","links":[],"anchors":{"convert-an-angle-to-a-vector2":{"type":"header","text":"Convert an angle to a Vector2","value":"convert-an-angle-to-a-vector2","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2},"javascript":{"type":"header","text":"Javascript","value":"javascript","line":19,"column":0,"depth":3},"convert-this-vector2-to-a-position":{"type":"header","text":"Convert this Vector2 to a position","value":"convert-this-vector2-to-a-position","line":32,"column":0,"depth":2},"convert-the-vector2-direction-to-an-angle":{"type":"header","text":"Convert the Vector2 direction to an angle","value":"convert-the-vector2-direction-to-an-angle","line":40,"column":0,"depth":2},"javascript-1":{"type":"header","text":"Javascript","value":"javascript-1","line":44,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"scpgtdyzfudnf17maue0y4f","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"convert-angle-to-vector2\">Convert Angle to Vector2<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#convert-angle-to-vector2\"></a></h1>\n<h2 id=\"convert-an-angle-to-a-vector2\">Convert an angle to a Vector2<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#convert-an-angle-to-a-vector2\"></a></h2>\n<p>If you have the angle you want to convert, you can use the cosinus and the sinus to obtain the angle's coordinates:</p>\n<p>x = cosinus(angle)\ny = sinus(angle)</p>\n<p>In mathematics, the cosinus would be the length of the bottom edge, and the sinus would provide the length of the opposite edge.</p>\n<p>In graphics, it become the coordinate of the vector.</p>\n<h3 id=\"javascript\">Javascript<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#javascript\"></a></h3>\n<pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token number\">90</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> vector <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">new</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Vector2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nvector<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">x</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token known-class-name class-name\">Math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">cos</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>angle<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\nvector<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">y</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token known-class-name class-name\">Math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">sin</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>angle<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n</code></pre>\n<p>Using the <a href=\"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Math\">Math built-in object</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"convert-this-vector2-to-a-position\">Convert this Vector2 to a position<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#convert-this-vector2-to-a-position\"></a></h2>\n<p>You can obtain a coordinate by multiplying the Vector2 by a length.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\"><span class=\"token keyword\">var</span> coordinate <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> vector <span class=\"token operator\">*</span> <span class=\"token number\">5</span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"convert-the-vector2-direction-to-an-angle\">Convert the Vector2 direction to an angle<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#convert-the-vector2-direction-to-an-angle\"></a></h2>\n<p>You can use atan2(y, x) to obtain the angle back.</p>\n<h3 id=\"javascript-1\">Javascript<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#javascript-1\"></a></h3>\n<pre class=\"language-javascript\"><code class=\"language-javascript\">\n<span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> angle <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token known-class-name class-name\">Math</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token method function property-access\">atan2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>vector<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">y</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> vector<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span><span class=\"token property-access\">x</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n</code></pre>","noteIndex":{"id":"os9ivsua46f0vj4p0yyqhx0","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1681658547293,"created":1676142715220,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"f2b2cb51b9be244f6389288b0e9baa6c","links":[],"anchors":{"awesome-knowledge":{"type":"header","text":"Awesome Knowledge","value":"awesome-knowledge","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1}},"children":["5vebznzkve1byblfc4hjnwb","ael2e6o55kce1nhvm90e3np"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Awesome Knowledge\n\nThis contains various knowledge on different topics.\n"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableSelfContainedVaults":true},"commands":{"lookup":{"note":{"select